        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "vehicle",
        "text": "On festival days, the people of Hillcross celebrate by launching gliders from the top of the cliffs and riding updrafts through the ravine. Hillcross gliders are made of bone and stretched hide, tied together with sinew, and sealed with a glue made from animal fat.",
